
== pair notre-dame / usc ==
    [notre-dame/usc 2015] ok: The 2015 Irish prevailed 41-31 under Brian Kelly to keep the Shillelagh during USC's post-sanctions rebuild.
    [notre-dame/usc 2019] ok: The 2019 meeting saw Brian Kelly's Notre Dame squad hold off USC by a 30-27 margin at Notre Dame Stadium.
    [notre-dame/usc 2014] ok: The 49-14 dismantling at the Coliseum gave USC its largest Jeweled Shillelagh margin in 40 years.
    [notre-dame/usc 2021] ok: Brian Kelly's final Notre Dame squad dispatched USC 31-16 in South Bend, closing out his tenure against the Trojans with a workmanlike win.
    [notre-dame/usc 2022] ok: Lincoln Riley's first Trojans handed Marcus Freeman's debut Irish a 38-27 defeat at Chicago's Soldier Field.
    [notre-dame/usc 2023] ok: Notre Dame's 48-2023 victory under Marcus Freeman marked the program's largest margin of victory in the rivalry since 2017.
    [notre-dame/usc 2024] ok: Freeman's Irish hung 49 points in the 2024 meeting, the most Notre Dame had scored against USC since 1972.
    [notre-dame/usc 2025] ok: Lincoln Riley's first defeat to Notre Dame came 34-24, sending the Jeweled Shillelagh back to South Bend.

== pair alabama / auburn ==
    [alabama/auburn 2015] ok: Alabama's 29-13 win at Bryant-Denny Stadium in 2015 featured Derrick Henry's 271 rushing yards, ending Auburn's three-game Iron Bowl win streak.
    [alabama/auburn 2020] ok: Nick Saban's Alabama clinched a playoff berth with a 42-13 dismantling of Gus Malzahn's Tigers.
    [alabama/auburn 2014] ok: Alabama's 55-44 shootout over Auburn in the 2014 Iron Bowl produced the rivalry's highest combined score at 99 points.
    [alabama/auburn 2021] ok: Alabama survived Auburn 24-22 in the 2021 Iron Bowl, a two-point margin in Bryan Harsin's first season on the Plains.
    [alabama/auburn 2022] ok: Nick Saban's Alabama dispatched Auburn 49-27 in the 2022 Iron Bowl, underscoring the widening competitive gap during Bryan Harsin's tumultuous tenure on the Plains.
    [alabama/auburn 2023] ok: Alabama escaped the Plains with a 27-24 victory in Nick Saban's final Iron Bowl.
    [alabama/auburn 2024] ok: Kalen DeBoer's first Iron Bowl resulted in a 28-14 Alabama victory that maintained the program's grip on the rivalry.
    [alabama/auburn 2025] ok: The 27-20 victory in Tuscaloosa gave Kalen DeBoer his second straight Iron Bowl win.

